def: An instrument for determining the rate of vibrations in tones.
One who, or that which, baffles.
Being under the apex; of or pertaining to the part just belowthe apex.

To draw tighter; to straiten; to make more close in any manner.Just where I please, with tightened rein I'll urge thee round thedusty plain. Fawkes.Tightening pulley (Mach.), a pulley which rests, or is forced,against a driving belt to tighten it.
Not fortunate; unsuccessful; not prosperous; unlucky; attendedwith misfortune; unhappy; as, an unfortunate adventure; anunfortunate man; an unfortunate commander; unfortunate business.-- n.

The width of the mouth when opened, as of birds, fishes, etc.GAPES; THE GAPESThe gapes.(a) A fit of yawning.(b) A disease of young poultry and other birds, attended with muchgaping. It is caused by a parasitic nematode worm (Syngamustrachealis), in the windpipe, which obstructs the breathing. SeeGapeworm.
The beam which supports the spindle socket of the runner in agrinding mill. Knight.
To remove from its actual century. [R.]It has first to uncentury itself. H. Drummond.
Any bird that frequents the water, or lives about rivers,lakes, etc., or on or near the sea; an aquatic fowl; -- used alsocollectively.
To draw air audibly up the nose; to snuff; -- sometimes done asa gesture of suspicion, offense, or contempt.So ye grow squeamish, gods, and sniff at heaven. M. Arnold.
Coupled without intermediate connections, as an engine and adynamo.
